<br>
As a player, I feel bad, 'cause I know how hard it can be to find a group, especially on this server with its low population. But if I compromised my character's IC views for the sake of accomodating other players, it'd make FV that much less of a roleplaying server for me. The best I can do is not actively hunt them down and try to force a confrontation/duel (which is what my character would oftentimes LIKE to do, damn softskins have no business on Kunark <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ), on the excuse that, &quot;Well, as long as it's not getting in my way or shooting its mouth off, there's no point in bothering with it. It's beneath my notice.&quot; And if I do challenge to duel and they refuse, it's, &quot;Oh, well, it's a coward, no honor to be had from killing it anyway.&quot;<br>
<br>
So, um, all I can say is, if you run into anyone in our guild and we're less-than-polite to you, it's nothing personal. You just don't have scales. Or you do have scales and you profess to like those who don't. We're not too keen on that, either. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
(Makes a note, I need to learn to speak Teir'Dal just for all the OOC apologies... hehe.)<br>
<br>
Voskor Oth<br>
