<br>
I don't know if this thread was actually soliciting advice about how to RP a jerk without annoying people ooc, but I've got at least one piece of advice to give, and one statement to make that hopefully people will take at face value and not get insulted by.<br>
<br>
Statement: Some people (seems like a lot, but that might just be the memories looming large) use RPing evil as an excuse to be assholes.  All kinds of anti-social behaviour ensues.  That doesn't sound like you in the least, the very fact that you are drawing a distincition proves that, but I thought I would point it out.  It is the reason for the following advice.<br>
<br>
Advice: With new people, when you are going to RP, send them a private tell explaining you are RPing.  I know, it really should not be necessary on an RP server, but them are the breaks.  Fortunately, you don't have to do it all the time with your regular friends.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Assuming a twisted little gnomish necro with delusions of adequecy ever makes friends....<br>
<br>
Thanks lots for being one of those people willing to both RP and make concessions to grouping dynamics.  My absolute favorite kind of people!  I find it's pretty common, also.  Tunare bless FV.  If not for this shard, I'd still be a retired EQer.  Though I sure did seem to get a lot more done when I was retired....  Oh well.<br>
<br>
In Service<br>
<br>
Valquiss Silverpalm <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukzanverto.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kzan Verto</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 79<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(1/14/02 12:43:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1109.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I'm not a jerk, I just play one in FV</span><hr size=1> I had a buddy who played a cleric as a complete ass. The story was my paladin and  this cleric were twin brothers and he eventually wound up chosing the path of evil (wound up building up his paineel faction and nuking his own Erudin guards. Eventually, he took the last name Kinslayer as opposed to my Kinsaver.<br>
<br>
Its hard to play an ass (well it was easy for him cuz he's an ass in real life &lt;grin&gt;) because some folks just can't help but take it personally. I hope you have fun and enjoy your stay on FV. But I hope you have a thick skin as well cuz some folks will just take your roleplaying the wrong way.<br>
<br>
Good Luck!<br>
